## Pending

Items below should be implemented when reaching the corresponding stage.

### After Optimization
- [ ] **Non-overlapping pair selection**: each ticker in at most 1 (or K) active pair(s). Use graph maximum matching weighted by expected return. Prevents concentration risk. Ref: Gatev et al. (2006).

### Phase 2
- [ ] **Phase 2a reassurance on 1h data** (730 days) — validate strategy across recent market events.
- [ ] **Phase 2b reassurance on 5m data** (60 days) — execution-level validation with the selected non-overlapping pairs.

### Future Enhancements
- [ ] **LLM-assisted strategy design**: feed pair statistics (spread distribution, half-life, volatility regime) to LLM. Build as Cursor skill or agent command.
- [ ] **Regime-adaptive parameters**: different z-score / window per volatility regime (low vol vs high vol).
- [ ] **Cointegration test (ADF on spread)**: the real pair selection criterion. Returns correlation is only a coarse pre-filter; cointegration validates that the spread is mean-reverting. Expected to reduce ~4K candidates to ~200-500.

## Design Decisions

Record the *why* behind key choices so future sessions have context.

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| Returns correlation over price correlation | Price correlation inflated by shared market trends over long periods |
| Adj Close for daily data | Splits/dividends create false spread signals without adjustment |
| 5m and 1h data also use Adj Close | Confirmed available via yfinance; consistent with Phase 1 |
| Phase 2 split into 2a (1h, 730d) + 2b (5m, 60d) | 60 days too short to capture market stress events; 1h interval allows 730 days from yfinance, covering recent volatility/rate events |
| Correlation band [0.40, 0.85] | Returns corr is a coarse filter only; real selection via cointegration. 0.40 = minimum daily co-movement signal (95th pct ≈ 0.50); 0.85 = exclude structurally identical instruments. Median returns corr across S&P 500 ≈ 0.31 over 26 years. |
| Pair-level overlap (min 5yr) over per-ticker date cutoff | Per-ticker MIN_HISTORY_START=2000 excluded GOOGL, TSLA, META etc. Pair-level overlap via corr(min_periods) is more flexible — newer stocks can pair with each other |
| Dual correlation condition (full + 3yr recent) | Catches pairs whose long-term relationship has degraded recently. If full-period corr is high but recent is low, the pair is excluded |
| Survivorship bias accepted | S&P 500 = survivors by definition; pairs trading trades current relationships |
| Non-overlapping selection deferred | Needs optimization results first; applied after parameter optimization, before Phase 2 |
